---
title: About Me
about: true
changefreq: monthly
priority: 0.8
layout: _layouts/default
---

<main class="info-block notch" id="main">
    <picture class="info-block__picture">
        <source media="(max-width: 39.9375em)" type="image/webp" srcset="https:{{aboutMe.heroImage.mobile}}?fm=webp">
        <source media="(max-width: 39.9375em)" srcset="https:{{aboutMe.heroImage.mobile}}">
        <source media="(min-width: 40em)" type="image/webp" srcset="https:{{aboutMe.heroImage.desktop}}?fm=webp">
        <source media="(min-width: 40em)" srcset="https:{{aboutMe.heroImage.desktop}}">
        <img class="info-block__picture-image" src="https:{{aboutMe.heroImage.desktop}}" alt="Wide shot of Alex Clapperton sat down working on his laptop.">
    </picture>

    <div class="info-block__inner">
        <h2 class="info-block__heading">Who am I?</h2>

        <p>I'm Alex, a Front-end Web Developer from the UK. My passion is to build beautiful and responsive websites with accessibility at the heart of it. I am currently working as a {{settings.jobTitle}} for <a class="link" href="{{settings.employerUrl}}" rel="external">{{settings.employer}}</a>, a digital agency based in Manchester.</p>

        <p>I thrive off learning new skills, being challenged daily and having to prove myself under pressure and being part of such young and dynamic industry is the perfect motivation for me to keep improving myself both professionally and personally.</p>

        <a class="info-block__button button button--primary" href="/contact/">
            Get in touch
            <svg class="button__icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24"><path fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 16.61l7.06 5.65 7.05-5.65m-7.05 5.65V2.5"/></svg>
        </a>
    </div>
</main>

<section class="blocks notch">
    <div class="blocks__container">
        <h3 class="blocks__heading hide" data-fade>Fun facts</h3>
        <p class="blocks__sub-text hide" data-fade>Here are some facts about me that I think you may find interesting and hopefully make you giggle along the way.</p>

        <div class="blocks__content">
            {{#each aboutMe.contentBlocks as |block|}}
                <div class="blocks__item hide" data-fade data-fade-delay="0.{{@index}}s">
                    <h4 class="blocks__item-title">{{{block.title}}}</h4>
                    <p class="blocks__item-body">{{block.body}}</p>
                </div>
            {{/each}}
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="articles notch">
    <div class="articles__container hide" data-fade>
        <small class="articles__heading-small">Read my</small>
        <h3 class="articles__heading-main">Latest articles</h3>
        <div class="articles__content">
        {{#eachUpTo collections.articles 3}}
            {{> _partials/articles }}
        {{/eachUpTo}}
        </div>
        <a class="button button--secondary" href="/articles/">
            View articles
            <svg class="button__icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24"><path fill="none" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4.5 16.61l7.06 5.65 7.05-5.65m-7.05 5.65V2.5"/></svg>
        </a>
    </div>
</section>
